        <hl1>When the Curtain Rises, I'll Still Be in Line</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Richard Schickel is not imagining things. People do stand in line just for the sake of standing in line. This phenomenon is not confined to Broadway.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Richard Schickel is not imagining things. People do stand in line just for the sake of standing in line. This phenomenon is not confined to Broadway.</p>
        <p>If you drove past any given bookstore at midnight on July 16, you would have seen a line of people of all ages, many of whom were up way past bedtime, standing and waiting for a book that probably won't go out of print for several generations.</p>
        <p>Fred Wemyss  Huntington, N.Y., July 20, 2005</p>
      </block>
